main event: An unidentified aerial phenomenon was reported in Newington, N.J. on 5 May 1959 at 2230 local time. The object appeared to have a white glowing rim with a dark center, exhibited rotating lights and emitted a high-pitched metallic sound as it moved from northeast to southwest.
interesting points: The sighting was reported by a credible source, Mr. G.M. 8, a resident of Newington, N.J.
The object's rotation, color, sound, and flight characteristics were noted to be unusual and set it apart from normal aircraft or other known aerial objects.
The document includes a communication report with details such as altitude, speed, and similar reports from a Navy pilot.

The report includes a standardized form with questions related to the observation, such as the appearance, size, and behavior of the object, as well as the witness's thoughts and actions at the time of the sighting.
There are references to potential collisions, evaluation of reliability of report sources, and requests for additional information, indicating a structured approach to investigating the sighting.
sighted object: unidentified aerial phenomenon with rotating lights and high-pitched metallic sound
